    <sect1 xml:id="sec-weblogic-install">
        <title>Oracle WebLogic Server 12cR2 Installation</title>
        <para>The following sections explain how to perform your Oracle
            WebLogic Server 12cR2 installation.</para>

        <sect2 xml:id="sec-weblogic-server">
            <title>Installing Oracle WebLogic Server Software</title>

            <para>Log in to the target system (&sls; 12 SP3 64-bit
                operating system) as a non-administration user. Download
                the Oracle WebLogic Server 12cR2 (12.2.1.2.0) from <link
                    xlink:href="http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/middleware/fusion-
                middleware/downloads/index.html"
                />. </para>

            <note>
                <title>Permissions</title>
                <para>Ensure the installation user has the proper
                    permissions to install and configure the
                    software.</para>
            </note>

            <para>Go to the directory where you downloaded the installation
                program. Extract the contents of the .zip archive
                <filename>fmw_12.2.1.2.0_wls_Disk1_1of1.zip</filename>)
                and launch the installation program by running
                    <command>java -jar fmw.xxxx.jar</command>.</para>

            <para>For the actual installation, follow the steps
                below:</para>

            <procedure>
                <step>
                    <para>Go to <emphasis role="strong">Installation
                            Inventory Setup</emphasis>.</para>
                    <figure>
                        <title>Installation Inventory Setup </title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installsetup.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installsetup.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>If this is your first Oracle installation on a
                        host that is running &sls;, use the
                            <emphasis>Oracle Fusion Middleware 12c
                            Installation Inventory Setup</emphasis> screen
                        to specify the location of the Oracle Central
                        Inventory Directory and Operating System Group
                        Name. Click <emphasis role="strong">OK</emphasis>
                        to continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Welcome</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Welcome</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installwelcome.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installwelcome.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>Review the information on this screen carefully
                        to be sure you have performed all the necessary
                        preparation steps. Click <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Next</emphasis> to continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Auto
                            Updates</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Auto Updates </title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installautoup.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installautoup.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>Select the option <emphasis role="strong">Skip
                            Auto Updates</emphasis>", to skip this screen.
                        Click <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis> to
                        continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Installation
                            Location</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Installation Location</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installloc.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installloc.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>Type the full path of the directory into the
                        Oracle Home field. Click <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Next</emphasis> to continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Installation
                            Type</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Installation Type</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installtype.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installtype.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>Use this screen to determine the type of
                        installation you want to perform, then click
                            <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis> to
                        continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Prerequisite
                            Checks</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Prerequisite Checks</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installprerequ.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installprerequ.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>The <emphasis role="strong">Prerequisite
                            Checks</emphasis> results will be shown as
                        above. Click <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Next</emphasis> to continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Security
                            Updates</emphasis> .</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Security Updates</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installsecup.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installsecup.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>If you want to register your installation, enter
                        your e-mail address and your <emphasis
                            role="strong">My Oracle Support</emphasis>
                        password.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Security Updates - 2</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installemail.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installemail.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>If you want to decline registration, deselect
                            <emphasis role="strong">I wish to receive
                            security updates via My Oracle
                            Support</emphasis> and confirm your choice.
                    </para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Installation
                            Summary </emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Installation Summary</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installsummary.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installsummary.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>This screen contains a list of the feature sets
                        you selected for your installation. It also contains the
                        approximate amount of disk space to be used by the
                        feature sets when the installation is complete.
                        Check the information, then click <emphasis
                            role="strong">Install</emphasis> to
                        continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Installation
                            Progress</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Installation Progress</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installprogress.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installprogress.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>This screen shows the progress of the
                        installation. When the progress bar reaches 100
                        percent, the installation is complete. Click
                            <emphasis role="strong">Finish</emphasis> to
                        continue.</para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Installation
                            Complete</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Installation Complete</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installcomplete.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-installcomplete.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>This screen appears at the conclusion of the
                        installation. Select the option<emphasis
                            role="strong">Automatically Launch the
                            Configuration Wizard</emphasis>, then click
                            <emphasis role="strong">Finish</emphasis> to
                        exit the installer.</para>
                </step>
            </procedure>
        </sect2>

        <sect2 xml:id="sec-weblogic-config">
            <title>Creating and Configuring the WebLogic Domain</title>

            <para>To start the domain configuration, you can choose from
                two options: </para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>From the last-shown screen <emphasis
                            role="strong">Installation Complete</emphasis>,
                        you can automatically launch the WebLogic
                        Configuration Wizard through the option <emphasis
                            role="strong">Automatically Launch the
                            Configuration Wizard</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>You can also navigate to the directory
                            <filename>ORACLE_HOME/oracle_common/common/bin</filename>
                        and start the WebLogic Server Configuration Wizard
                        by running the command
                            <command>./config.sh</command>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>

            <para>To set up your configuration, follow the steps
                below:</para>

            <procedure>
                <step>
                    <para>Go to <emphasis role="strong">Configuration
                            Type</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Configuration Type</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-configtype.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-configtype.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>Select the option <emphasis role="strong">Create
                            a New Domain</emphasis> and specify the Domain
                        home directory in the <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Domain Location</emphasis> field. Click
                            <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis> to
                        continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Templates</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Templates</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-templates.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-templates.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>On the <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Templates</emphasis> screen select <emphasis
                            role="strong">Basic WebLogic Server
                            Domain</emphasis> which is pre-selected by
                        default. In addition, select <emphasis role="strong">WebLogic
                            Coherence Cluster Extension</emphasis> for the
                        configuration. Click <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Next</emphasis> to continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Administrator
                            Account</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Administrator Account</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-adminaccount.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-adminaccount.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>Specify the user name and password for the
                        default WebLogic Administrator account for the
                        domain. Click <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Next</emphasis> to continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Domain Mode
                            and JDK</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Domain Mode and JDK</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-domain.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-domain.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>Select <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Development</emphasis> in the Domain Mode
                        field and <emphasis role="strong">Oracle
                            HotSpot</emphasis> in the JDK field. Click
                            <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis> to
                        continue.</para>

                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Advanced
                            Configuration</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Advanced Configuration</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-advancedconfig.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-advancedconfig.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>According to your requirements, select the
                        desired options on the <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Advanced Configuration</emphasis> screen.
                        Click <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis> to
                        continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Configuration
                            Summary</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Configuration Summary</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-configsummary.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-configsummary.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>Review the information on the <emphasis
                            role="strong">Configuration Summary</emphasis>
                        screen to verify everything is correct. Click
                            <emphasis role="strong">Create</emphasis> to
                        continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">Configuration
                            Progress</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>Configuration Progress</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-configprogress.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-configprogress.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>The <emphasis role="strong">Configuration
                            Progress</emphasis> screen shows the progress
                        of your configuration. For different progress
                        states, different messages are displayed. When you
                        see the message <emphasis role="strong">Domain
                            Created successfully</emphasis>", click
                            <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis> to
                        continue.</para>
                </step>

                <step>
                    <para>Proceed to <emphasis role="strong">End Of
                            Configuration</emphasis>.</para>

                    <figure>
                        <title>End of Configuration</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject role="fo">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-endconfig.png"
                                    width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <imageobject role="html">
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-endconfig.png"
                                    width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>

                    <para>When you see the message <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Oracle WebLogic Server Configuration
                            Succeeded</emphasis>, record the <emphasis
                            role="strong">Domain Location</emphasis> and
                            <emphasis role="strong">Admin Server
                            URL</emphasis>. Click <emphasis role="strong"
                            >Finish</emphasis> to exit the Configuration
                        Wizard.</para>
                </step>
            </procedure>
        </sect2>

        <sect2 xml:id="sec-start-adminserver">
            <title>Starting the Administration Server and Verifying the
                Configuration</title>

            <para>To start the Administration Server through a terminal, go
                to the <filename>DOMAIN_HOME/bin</filename> directory and
                run the command <command>./startWebLogic.sh</command>
                .</para>

            <figure>
                <title>Starting the Administration Server</title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject role="fo">
                        <imagedata
                            fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-adminservterminal.png"
                            width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <imageobject role="html">
                        <imagedata
                            fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-adminservterminal.png"
                            width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>

            <para>Review the information displayed on the screen.</para>


            <para>Access the Oracle WebLogic Server Administration
                Console.</para>

            <figure>
                <title>Oracle WebLogic Server Administration
                    Console</title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject role="fo">
                        <imagedata fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-loginpage.png"
                            width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <imageobject role="html">
                        <imagedata fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-loginpage.png"
                            width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>

            <para>Fill in your user name and password. You are then
                proceeded to the <emphasis role="strong">WebLogic Server
                    12cR2 Administration Console</emphasis> home
                page.</para>

            <figure>
                <title>Oracle WebLogic Server Administration Console Home
                    Page</title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject role="fo">
                        <imagedata fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-homepage.png"
                            width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <imageobject role="html">
                        <imagedata fileref="oracle-webl-sles12sp3-homepage.png"
                            width="80%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>

            <para>The installation and configuration of your Oracle
                WebLogic Server 12cR2 is now successfully finished.</para>

        </sect2>
